{"title_page": "Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox football club\n |clubname = UCV\n |image    = Universidad Cesar Vallejo.svg\n |image_size = 200px\n |fullname = Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo\n |nickname = ''Los Poetas'' (The Poets)\n |founded  = January 6, 1996\n |ground   = Estadio Municipal de Casa Grande,<br />[[Trujillo, Peru]]\n |capacity = 8,000\n |chrtitle = President\n |chairman = {{flagicon|Peru}} Cesar Acu\u00f1a Peralta\n |manager  = {{flagicon|Peru}} [[Jos\u00e9 del Solar]]\n | league = [[Torneo Descentralizado|Liga 1]]\n | season = [[2019 Liga 1 (Peru)|2019]]\n | position = Liga 1, 8th\n |website  = http://www.ucvclub.com/\n|pattern_la1=_ucv19h|pattern_b1=_ucv19h|pattern_ra1=_ucv19h|pattern_sh1=_ucv19h|pattern_so1=_ucv19h|\n|leftarm1=00366C|body1=00366C|rightarm1=00366C|shorts1=00366C|socks1=00366C\n|pattern_la2=_ucv19a|pattern_b2=_ucv19a|pattern_ra2=_ucv19a|pattern_sh2=_ucv19a|pattern_so2=_ucv19a\n|leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=ffffFF|rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=FFFFFF\n|pattern_la3=|pattern_b3=|pattern_ra3=|pattern_sh3=\n|leftarm3=|body3=|rightarm3=|shorts3=|socks3=\n}}\n\n'''Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo''' is a [[Peru]]vian [[association football|football club]] located in [[Trujillo, Peru|Trujillo]]. The club was founded on January 6, 1996 and was promoted in 2003, through the [[Copa Per\u00fa]], to the [[Peruvian First Division]] and relegated in 2005. In 2007, they were [[Peruvian Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] champions and were promoted to the first division again.\n\n==History==\nThe club was founded on January 6, 1996 representing [[Cesar Vallejo University]] and first participated in the championship of the third division of Trujillo at the end of 1996 and the team managed to crown champion of the tournament in 1997. In the year 1998, champion of the second division was crowned of [[Trujillo Province, Peru|Trujillo]] and won the privilege to participate, at the age of two years since foundation. Vallejo participated for the first time in the tournament of first division in the year 1999. They did quite well and even occupied the third position of the tournament. In its second year in first division, Vallejo had the respect of the large teams of the city was won of Trujillo, like the [[Carlos A. Mannucci]], [[Sport Coopsol Trujillo|Universidad Privada Antenor Orrego]], [[Alfonso Ugarte de Chicl\u00edn|Alfonso Ugarte]], among others. To surprise of many came, they fight the title with the Universidad Priavada Antenor Orrego and achieved the subchampionship.\n\nIn its campaign 2001 came be Departamental, Provincial, and Local champion. In the regional phase of the [[Copa Per\u00fa]], was faced to the traditional [[Universidad T\u00e9cnica de Cajamarca]] and [[Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez FBC]] of [[Chimbote]] to whom was defeated. Then, in the encounters by the national phase left on the road to the [[Atl\u00e9tico Grau]] and in the great end the Poets fell for penalties and [[Coronel Bolognesi]] went on to win the [[Peru Cup]].\n\nThe following year would repeat a great campaign but on the national phase [[Atl\u00e9tico Grau]] would leave it on the road. In the 2003 it achieved the desired title and its income increased after facing to worthy rival of different regions of the country and to conquer in the great end to the [[Deportivo Educaci\u00f3n]] of [[Abancay]] in the National Stadium.\n\nThe club struggled during the 2004 and 2005 seasons in the first division and was relegated to 2nd division. During the 2007 season, the club participate in the Second Division of the Peruvian soccer, in which it obtained promotion back to top division, after participating against teams as [[Deportivo Universidad San Marcos|Universidad San Marcos]], [[Hijos de Acosvinchos]], [[Universidad T\u00e9cnica de Cajamarca]] and [[Atl\u00e9tico Minero]]. In November 2012 the club qualified for the edition 2013 of the [[Copa Libertadores]] where they were eliminated in the preliminary round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://laindustria.pe/deportes/futbol-nacional/cesar-vallejo-clasifico-la-copa-libertadores|title=C\u00e9sar Vallejo clasific\u00f3 a la Copa Libertadores|accessdate=November 19, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120034413/http://laindustria.pe/deportes/futbol-nacional/cesar-vallejo-clasifico-la-copa-libertadores|archive-date=November 20, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> During the 2013 season it qualified to the [[2014 Copa Sudamericana]] after finishing 5th.\n\nOn 27 April 2015, they won the 2015 [[Torneo del Inca]] as they beat [[Alianza Lima]] 1\u20133 with goals of [[Mauricio Montes]], [[V\u00edctor Cedr\u00f3n]] and [[Daniel Ch\u00e1vez]]. This is Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo first major title.\n\n==Colours and badge==\nThe club's colors are blue, white and red just as the [[Cesar Vallejo University|university's]] colours. Since its promotion to the first division, the club has used three badges. The first badge had the club's initials with the university's name along the oval-shaped outline and lasted until 2009. The second badge only modified the center of the badge by adding a book next to the initials of the club and was first used in 2010. The third badge was a complete change, taking the shape of shield with the red claws of a [[griffin]] placed on the top. The significance of the griffin is due to the city of [[Trujillo, Peru|Trujillo]] coat of arms displaying one.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u00bfSabes qu\u00e9 hizo el club C\u00e9sar Vallejo con su insignia?|url=http://depor.pe/futbol-peruano/902001/noticia-sabes-que-hizo-cesar-vallejo-su-insignia|work=depor.pe|accessdate=3 August 2013|language=Spanish|date=27 December 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121231134158/http://depor.pe/futbol-peruano/902001/noticia-sabes-que-hizo-cesar-vallejo-su-insignia|archive-date=December 31, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> Moreover, the badge employed by the football club displays the team name as Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo Club de F\u00fatbol to distinguish it from the club's other sports teams.\n\n<center>\n<gallery>\nFile:Universidad_C\u00e9sar_Vallejo.png|Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo's badge, 1996\u201309\nFile:UCV logo 2010.png|Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo's badge, 2010\u201312\n</gallery>\n</center>\n\n==Honours==\n===National===\n====League====\n*'''[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Peruana|Peruvian Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]]:'''\n::'''Winners (2)''': [[2007 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Peruana|2007]], [[2018 Peruvian Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2018]]\n::''Runner-up (1):'' [[2017 Peruvian Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2017]]\n\n*'''[[Copa Per\u00fa]]:'''\n::'''Winners (1)''': [[2003 Copa Per\u00fa|2003]]\n::''Runner-up (1):'' [[2001 Copa Per\u00fa|2001]]\n\n====National cups====\n*'''[[Torneo del Inca]]: '''\n::'''Winners (1)''': [[2015 Torneo del Inca|2015]]\n\n===Regional===\n*'''[[Copa Per\u00fa|Regi\u00f3n II]]:'''\n::'''Winners (3)''': [[2001 Copa Per\u00fa|2001]], [[2002 Copa Per\u00fa|2002]], [[2003 Copa Per\u00fa|2003]]\n\n*'''[[Ligas Departamentales del Peru|Liga Departamental de La Libertad]]:'''\n::'''Winners (3)''': 2001, 2002, 2003\n\n*'''[[Ligas Provinciales del Peru|Liga Provincial de Trujillo]]:'''\n::'''Winners (1)''': 2001\n\n*'''[[Ligas Distritales del Peru|Liga Distrital de Trujillo]]:'''\n::'''Winners (1)''': 2001\n::''Runner-up (1):'' 2000\n\n===Friendly International===\n*'''[[Copa Ciudad de Trujillo]]: '''\n::'''Winners (1)''': [[Copa Ciudad de Trujillo#2011 Copa Ciudad de Trujillo|2011]]\n\n===Under-20 team===\n*'''[[Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva]]: '''\n::'''Winners (1)''': [[2010 Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva|2010]]\n\n==Performance in CONMEBOL competitions==\n*'''[[Copa Libertadores]]: 1 appearance'''\n::[[2013 Copa Sudamericana|2013]]: First Stage\n\n*'''[[Copa Sudamericana]]: 2 appearances'''\n::[[2010 Copa Sudamericana|2010]]: First Round\n::[[2011 Copa Sudamericana|2011]]: First Round\n::[[2014 Copa Sudamericana|2014]]: Quarter-finals\n\n==Current squad==\n{{updated|19 August 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clubdeportivoucv.edu.pe/plantel-2012|accessdate=April 2, 2012|title=Plantel 2012|publisher=CD Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo|language=spanish|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321173100/http://www.clubdeportivoucv.edu.pe/plantel-2012|archive-date=March 21, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|nat=Peru|name=[[Ra\u00fal Fern\u00e1ndez Valverde|Ra\u00fal Fern\u00e1ndez]]|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|nat=Peru|name=[[Edgar Villamar\u00edn]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|nat=Argentina|name=[[Leandro Fleitas]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|nat=Peru|name= Jorge R\u00edos|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|nat=Peru|name= Renzo Garc\u00e9s|pos=DF|other=on loan from [[Sporting Cristal]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|nat=Peru|name=[[Carlos Orejuela]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|nat=Argentina|name= [[Germ\u00e1n Pacheco]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|nat=Uruguay|name=[[Santiago Silva Gerez|Santiago Silva]]|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|nat=Peru|name=[[Alexander S\u00e1nchez]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|nat=Peru|name= Raziel Garc\u00eda|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|nat=Peru|name= M\u00e1ximo Rabines|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|nat=Peru|name= Anthony Gordillo|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|nat=Peru|name=[[Pedro Paulo Requena|Pedro Requena]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=15|nat=Peru|name= Jeremy Rostaing|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|nat=Peru|name= \u00c1lvaro Medrano|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|nat=Peru|name=[[V\u00edctor Cedr\u00f3n]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=20|nat=Peru|name= Arly Benites|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|nat=Peru|name= Juan Pretel|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|nat=Peru|name= Franco Medina|pos=DF|other=on loan from [[Alianza Lima]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=23|nat=Peru|name=[[Ronald Quinteros]]|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=25|nat=Peru|name= Frank Ysique|pos=MF|other=on loan from [[Sporting Cristal]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=27|nat=Peru|name= Rolando D\u00edaz|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=28|nat=Peru|name=[[Elsar Rodas]]|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=30|nat=Peru|name= Alexis Rojas|pos=MF|other=on loan from [[Sporting Cristal]]}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n==Notable players==\n{{for|a list of all former and current CD Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo players with a Wikipedia article|Category:Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo footballers}}\n\n==Managers==\n*{{flagicon|Peru}} [[Franco Navarro]] (2005)\n*{{flagicon|Peru}} [[:es:Roberto Arrelucea|Roberto Arrelucea]] (2007\u2013May 8)\n*{{flagicon|Peru}} [[V\u00edctor Rivera (football manager)|V\u00edctor Rivera]] (Dec 15, 2010\u2013??)\n*{{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[Mario Viera]] (July 2011\u20131?)\n*{{flagicon|Peru}} [[Franco Navarro]] (Dec 6, 2013\u201314)\n*{{flagicon|Argentina}} [[\u00c1ngel Comizzo]] (2016)\n*{{flagicon|Colombia}} Francisco Cort\u00e9s (2017)\n*{{flagicon|Peru}} [[Jos\u00e9 del Solar]] (2018-)\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of football clubs in Peru]]\n*[[Peruvian football league system]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110806181307/http://www.clubdeportivoucv.edu.pe/ Official website]\n*{{Facebook|215296224645}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n*{{YouTube|user=clubucv}}\n\n{{Primera Divisi\u00f3n Peruana}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Universidad Cesar Vallejo}}\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1996]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Trujillo, Peru]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Peru]]\n[[Category:University and college association football clubs]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox football club\n |clubname = UCV\n |image    = Universidad Cesar Vallejo.svg\n |image_size = 200px\n |fullname = Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo\n |nickname = ''Los Poetas'' (The Poets)\n |founded  = January 6, 1996\n |ground   = Estadio Municipal de Casa Grande,<br />[[Trujillo, Peru]]\n |capacity = 8,000\n |chrtitle = President\n |chairman = {{flagicon|Peru}} Cesar Acu\u00f1a Peralta\n |manager  = {{flagicon|Peru}} [[Jos\u00e9 del Solar]]\n | league = [[Torneo Descentralizado|Liga 1]]\n | season = [[2019 Liga 1 (Peru)|2019]]\n | position = Liga 1, 8th\n |website  = http://www.ucvclub.com/\n|pattern_la1=_ucv19h|pattern_b1=_ucv19h|pattern_ra1=_ucv19h|pattern_sh1=_ucv19h|pattern_so1=_ucv19h|\n|leftarm1=00366C|body1=00366C|rightarm1=00366C|shorts1=00366C|socks1=00366C\n|pattern_la2=_ucv19a|pattern_b2=_ucv19a|pattern_ra2=_ucv19a|pattern_sh2=_ucv19a|pattern_so2=_ucv19a\n|leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=ffffFF|rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=FFFFFF\n|pattern_la3=|pattern_b3=|pattern_ra3=|pattern_sh3=\n|leftarm3=|body3=|rightarm3=|shorts3=|socks3=\n}}\n\n'''Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo''' is a [[Peru]]vian [[association football|football club]] located in [[Trujillo, Peru|Trujillo]]. The club was founded on January 6, 1996 and was promoted in 2003, through the [[Copa Per\u00fa]], to the [[Peruvian First Division]] and relegated in 2005. In 2007, they were [[Peruvian Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] champions and were promoted to the first division again.\n\n==History==\nThe club was founded on January 6, 1996 representing [[Cesar Vallejo University]] and first participated in the championship of the third division of Trujillo at the end of 1996 and the team managed to crown champion of the tournament in 1997. In the year 1998, champion of the second division was crowned of [[Trujillo Province, Peru|Trujillo]] and won the privilege to participate, at the age of two years since foundation. Vallejo participated for the first time in the tournament of first division in the year 1999. They did quite well and even occupied the third position of the tournament. In its second year in first division, Vallejo had the respect of the large teams of the city was won of Trujillo, like the [[Carlos A. Mannucci]], [[Sport Coopsol Trujillo|Universidad Privada Antenor Orrego]], [[Alfonso Ugarte de Chicl\u00edn|Alfonso Ugarte]], among others. To surprise of many came, they fight the title with the Universidad Priavada Antenor Orrego and achieved the subchampionship.\n\nIn its campaign 2001 came be Departamental, Provincial, and Local champion. In the regional phase of the [[Copa Per\u00fa]], was faced to the traditional [[Universidad T\u00e9cnica de Cajamarca]] and [[Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez FBC]] of [[Chimbote]] to whom was defeated. Then, in the encounters by the national phase left on the road to the [[Atl\u00e9tico Grau]] and in the great end the Poets fell for penalties and [[Coronel Bolognesi]] went on to win the [[Peru Cup]].\n\nThe following year would repeat a great campaign but on the national phase [[Atl\u00e9tico Grau]] would leave it on the road. In the 2003 it achieved the desired title and its income increased after facing to worthy rival of different regions of the country and to conquer in the great end to the [[Deportivo Educaci\u00f3n]] of [[Abancay]] in the National Stadium.\n\nThe club struggled during the 2004 and 2005 seasons in the first division and was relegated to 2nd division. During the 2007 season, the club participate in the Second Division of the Peruvian soccer, in which it obtained promotion back to top division, after participating against teams as [[Deportivo Universidad San Marcos|Universidad San Marcos]], [[Hijos de Acosvinchos]], [[Universidad T\u00e9cnica de Cajamarca]] and [[Atl\u00e9tico Minero]]. In November 2012 the club qualified for the edition 2013 of the [[Copa Libertadores]] where they were eliminated in the preliminary round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://laindustria.pe/deportes/futbol-nacional/cesar-vallejo-clasifico-la-copa-libertadores|title=C\u00e9sar Vallejo clasific\u00f3 a la Copa Libertadores|accessdate=November 19, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120034413/http://laindustria.pe/deportes/futbol-nacional/cesar-vallejo-clasifico-la-copa-libertadores|archive-date=November 20, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> During the 2013 season it qualified to the [[2014 Copa Sudamericana]] after finishing 5th.\n\nOn 27 April 2015, they won the 2015 [[Torneo del Inca]] as they beat [[Alianza Lima]] 1\u20133 with goals of [[Mauricio Montes]], [[V\u00edctor Cedr\u00f3n]] and [[Daniel Ch\u00e1vez]]. This is Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo first major title.\n\n==Colours and badge==\nThe club's colors are blue, white and red just as the [[Cesar Vallejo University|university's]] colours. Since its promotion to the first division, the club has used three badges. The first badge had the club's initials with the university's name along the oval-shaped outline and lasted until 2009. The second badge only modified the center of the badge by adding a book next to the initials of the club and was first used in 2010. The third badge was a complete change, taking the shape of shield with the red claws of a [[griffin]] placed on the top. The significance of the griffin is due to the city of [[Trujillo, Peru|Trujillo]] coat of arms displaying one.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u00bfSabes qu\u00e9 hizo el club C\u00e9sar Vallejo con su insignia?|url=http://depor.pe/futbol-peruano/902001/noticia-sabes-que-hizo-cesar-vallejo-su-insignia|work=depor.pe|accessdate=3 August 2013|language=Spanish|date=27 December 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121231134158/http://depor.pe/futbol-peruano/902001/noticia-sabes-que-hizo-cesar-vallejo-su-insignia|archive-date=December 31, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> Moreover, the badge employed by the football club displays the team name as Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo Club de F\u00fatbol to distinguish it from the club's other sports teams.\n\n<center>\n<gallery>\nFile:Universidad_C\u00e9sar_Vallejo.png|Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo's badge, 1996\u201309\nFile:UCV logo 2010.png|Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo's badge, 2010\u201312\n</gallery>\n</center>\n\n==Honours==\n===National===\n====League====\n*'''[[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n Peruana|