1.pdf|title=Top 10 Sales in Europe|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=11|issue=21|page=24|date=May 21, 1994|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|1|year=1994|week=23|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|4|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Poland ([[Lista Przeboj\u00f3w Programu Trzeciego|LP3]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://lp3.polskieradio.pl/notowania/?rok=1994&numer=641|title=Notowanie nr641|publisher=[[Lista Przeboj\u00f3w Programu Trzeciego|LP3]]|language=Polish|date=May 27, 1994|accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n| 14\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|5|date=19940416|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|AFYVE]])<ref>{{cite book |last=Salaverri|first=Fernando|title=S\u00f3lo \u00e9xitos: a\u00f1o a a\u00f1o, 1959\u20132002|edition=1st |date=September 2005|publisher=Fundaci\u00f3n Autor-SGAE|location=Spain|isbn=84-8048-639-2}}</ref> \n| 1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|13|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKsinglesbyname|1|artist=Prince|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 2, 2016}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=Hot 100}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: The Billboard Hot 100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B Singles]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=R&B/Hip-Hop Songs}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Mainstream Top 40]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=Pop Songs}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: Pop Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Rhythmic (chart)|Rhythmic Top 40]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=Rhythmic Top 40}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: Rhythmic Top 40|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 3\n|}\n\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1994)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia (ARIA)<ref name=\"ausye\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/annual-charts/1994/singles-chart|title=1994 ARIA Singles Chart|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]]|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| 23\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Belgium (Ultratop Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1994|title=jaaroverzichten 1994|language=Dutch|publisher=Ultratop|accessdate=December 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| 16\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.2687&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.2687.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.2687|title=RPM Top 100 Hit Tracks of 1994|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]]|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| 41\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Europe (Eurochart Hot 100)<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1994/MM-1994-12-24.pdf|title=1994 Year-End Sales Charts: Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|accessdate=November 28, 2019|work=Music & Media|format=PDF}}</ref> \n| 17\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|France (SNEP)<ref>1994 French Singles Chart [http://www.disqueenfrance.com/fr/monopage.xml?id=259376&year=1994 Disqueenfrance.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110820065025/http://www.disqueenfrance.com/fr/monopage.xml?id=259376&year=1994 |date=2011-08-20 }} (Retrieved January 30, 2009)</ref>\n| 28\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1994|title=Top 100 Singles \u2013 Jahrescharts 1994|language=German|publisher=[[GfK Entertainment]]|accessdate=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n| 46\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.top40web.nl/jaarlijsten/jr1994.html|title=Jaarlijsten 1994|language=Dutch|publisher=Stichting Nederlandse Top 40|accessdate=November 29, 2019}}</ref>\n| 6\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1994&cat=s|title=JAAROVERZICHTEN - Single 1994|language=Dutch|publisher=dutchcharts.nl|accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|New Zealand (Recorded Music NZ)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/index.php/chart/?chart=3883|title=End of Year Charts 1994|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Sweden (Sverigetopplistan)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/43?dspy=1994&dspp=1|title=\u00c5rslista Singlar, 1994|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|language=Swedish|accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n| 76\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/charts/jahreshitparade/1994|title=SCHWEIZER JAHRESHITPARADE 1994|accessdate=December 4, 2019|publisher=hitparade.ch}}</ref> \n| 15\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1994|title=''Billboard'' Top 100 Hits for 1994|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref>\n| 19\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Mayte version==\n[[Mayte Garcia]] later recorded her own version called \"The Most Beautiful Boy in the World\". The song appears on her album ''[[Child of the Sun (album)|Child of the Sun]]''. It has the same instrumental backing track with extra reverb, and her vocals, with a few slight ad-lib changes. It was released by [[NPG Records]].\n\n==Cover versions==\n*In 1998, rapper [[Raheem the Dream]] sampled the song to make his own track, also titled \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\".{{cn|date=April 2018}}\n*In 2003, pianist [[Alex Bugnon]] covered the song on his album ''Southern Living''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.narada.com/images/AlbumPage/SouthernLiving/southernliving_page.htm|title=Southern Living|publisher=[[Narada Productions|Narada.com]]|accessdate=March 31, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706204534/http://www.narada.com/images/AlbumPage/SouthernLiving/southernliving_page.htm|archivedate=July 6, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://jazztimes.com/reviews/currents/alex-bugnon-southern-living/|title=Southern Living Alex Bugnon|magazine=[[JazzTimes|JazzTimes.com]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n*In 2013, artist [[Bruno Mars]] covered the song during [[The Moonshine Jungle Tour]].{{cn|date=April 2018}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n*Uptown: ''The Vault \u2013 The Definitive Guide to the Musical World of Prince'': Nilsen Publishing 2004, {{ISBN|91-631-5482-X}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Prince singles}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Most Beautiful Girl In The World, The}}\n[[Category:1994 singles]]\n[[Category:Prince (musician) songs]]\n[[Category:Pop ballads]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Prince (musician)]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Dutch Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Single Top 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Spain]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:1990s ballads]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Prince (musician)]]\n[[Category:NPG Records singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Prince (musician)]]\n[[Category:1993 songs]]\n[[Category:Contemporary R&B ballads]]\n[[Category:American soft rock songs]]\n[[Category:Rock ballads]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup|date=May 2019|reason=The recently added paragraph on the plagiarism needs a rewrite}}{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\n| cover      = PrinceTheMostBeautifulGirlInTheWorld.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]\n| album      = [[The Beautiful Experience]] ''and'' [[The Gold Experience]]\n| B-side     = {{ubl|\"Beautiful\"|\"Beautiful\" (Extended Club Mix by [[Simon Harris (musician)|Simon Harris]]) <small>(UK 12\")</small>|\"Beautiful Beats\" <small>(UK 12\")</small>}}\n| released   = February 24, 1994\n| format     = 7\" single<br>[[12-inch single|12\" single]]<br>[[Cassette single]]<br>[[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 1993\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Soft rock]]|[[contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[pop music|pop]]}}\n| length     = 4:07 (single edit)<br>4:37 (original mix)<br>4:25 (''Gold Experience'' version)\n| label      = [[NPG Records|NPG]], [[Bellmark Records|Bellmark]], [[Edel AG|Edel]]\n| writer     = Prince\n| producer   = Prince, Ricky Peterson\n| prev_title = [[Peach (Prince song)|Peach]]\n| prev_year  = 1993\n| next_title = [[Pope (Prince song)|Pope]]\n| next_year  = 1994\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{Youtube|-mATCxIqOjg|\u00abThe Most Beautiful Girl in The World\u00bb}}}}\n  {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = Prince (UK)\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Controversy (song)|Controversy]]\n | prev_year  = 1993\n | title      = The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\n | year       = 1994\n | next_title = [[Letitgo (song)|Letitgo]]\n | next_year  = 1994\n}}\n}}{{List|Liza Hopkins=My love|date=November 2016}}\n\n\"'''The Most Beautiful Girl in the World'''\" is the lead single from the 1994 EP ''[[The Beautiful Experience]]'' by [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], and his 1995 album ''[[The Gold Experience]]''. In his singles chronology, it was his third major release since changing his stage name to \"The Artist Formerly Known As Prince\" or \"TAFKAP.\" In his albums chronology, it along with the EP was his second release after changing his name. With the consent of Prince's usual record distributor [[Warner Bros. Records]], \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" was released by [[NPG Records]] and [[Edel Music]], and independently distributed by [[Bellmark Records]], under the control and guidance of [[Music of Life]], as a one-off single, topping five different charts.\n\nThe single was released in February 1994 in the United Kingdom, and remains Prince's only number one single in the [[UK Singles Chart]],<ref name=\"British Hit Singles & Albums\">{{cite book|first=David|last=Roberts|year=2006|title=[[British Hit Singles & Albums]]|edition=19th|publisher=Guinness World Records Limited|location= London|isbn=1-904994-10-5|page=565}}</ref> and was shortly followed by an [[Extended play|EP]] of [[remix]]es titled ''[[The Beautiful Experience]]'' that also charted on #18 in the chart in the United Kingdom. The version that was released on ''The Gold Experience'' is a different mix of the song.\n\nThere has been a long running copyright dispute since 1995 and a court in Italy ruled that Prince had plagiarized the song, giving writing credit to those other than Prince. <ref> https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7445762/princes-italian-plagiarism-case</ref>\n\n==Development==\nThe original track is a slow-grooving [[ballad]] that serenades a beautiful woman, his soon-to-be fianc\u00e9, [[Mayte Garcia]]. The song was played during the [[Miss USA]] pageant in 1994, but not in full. It was widely advertised in news and trade magazines that a new song from Prince would be premiered at the pageant. The ads had Prince sitting in a chair with a hat pulled down over his face, and Garcia standing next to his chair. The song was officially released on February 24, 1994. It later appeared on ''[[The Gold Experience]]''.\n\nThe version on ''The Gold Experience'' is remixed. The drums are more crisp in the mix, and there are slight instrumental changes. There are also added sound effects and instrumental breaks in the second version. The bridge is slightly more robust as well. The song is still based in light [[guitar]], [[Electronic keyboard|keyboards]] and live [[Drum kit|drums]]. Although most of the song is sung in falsetto with Prince reaching some extremely high notes, the final bridge has him using his regular voice as well as a lower baritone range in one small segment.\n\nThe song was a worldwide hit and established Prince's ability to succeed commercially under his new name, peaking at No. 3 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. It was certified [[RIAA certification|gold]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]] and sold 700,000 copies domestically.<ref>{{cite certification|region=United States|artist=Prince|title=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uAsEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA57|title=Best-Selling Records of 1994|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=BPI Communications|date=January 21, 1995|page=57|issn=0006-2510|volume=107|number=3}}</ref> However, the song was his last top 10 hit on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 during his lifetime.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Trust |first1=Gary |title=Desiigner Holds Off Drake Atop Hot 100, Prince & Beyonce Hit Top 10 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7350427/desiigner-drake-hot-100-prince-beyonce-top-10 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard.com]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |date=2016-05-02}}</ref> \n\nIt became his first and only United Kingdom No. 1 single under any name as a performer.<ref name=\"British Hit Singles & Albums\"/> He did have two other United Kingdom number ones as a songwriter: the 1984 hit single \"[[I Feel for You]]\" covered by [[Chaka Khan]] and [[Sin\u00e9ad O'Connor]]'s 1990 cover of \"[[Nothing Compares 2 U]]\". Prince danced to his own song \"The Most Beautiful Girl In The World\" after the World Music Awards at an after show event with Kylie Minogue in 1994.\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[AllMusic]] editor Daniel Browne called it a \"dreamy slice of soul-pop in the style of [[The Delfonics|Delfonics]] mastermind [[Thom Bell]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-beautiful-experience-ep-mw0000115622|title=Prince - The Beautiful Experience EP|work=AllMusic|date=|accessdate=2020-02-18}}</ref> Editor [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] wrote in his review of ''[[The Gold Experience]]'', that it has a \"more immediate\" melody and described it as a \"the Philly soul tribute\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/gold-experience-mw0000121276|title=Prince - Gold Experience|work=AllMusic|date=|accessdate=2020-02-18}}</ref> ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cashbox]]'' wrote about the song, \"Never one to sit idly by. Prince returns after a short sabbatical with this new funky single, released through a new deal with A1 Bell's Bellmark Records (...) Already making waves at Urban and top-40 radio, this keyboard-heavy, lushly produced track breaks no new ground for Prince, but looks like a sure bet for chart success. Expect to hear this song of female worship at the junior prom come June.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Cash-Box/90s/1994/CB-1994-03-12.pdf|title=Pop Singles: Reviews|publisher=Cashbox magazine|page=11|accessdate=2020-01-21}}</ref> Tom Ewing from [[Freaky Trigger]] described the song as a \"high, heady, perfume-drunk ballad drawing from the well of Thom Bell's work with the Delfonics and [[The Stylistics|Stylistics]].\" He added, \"Prince disciplines himself, staying almost throughout at the absolute top of his register, a high-wire act he pulls off without a hitch but also without any moment which completely sells the decision. The music is opulent boudoir funk, the best line \u2013 \"How can I get through days when I can't get through hours?\" \u2013 is very good, and there's a casual classiness to the record.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freakytrigger.co.uk/popular/2013/01/the-artist-formerly-known-as-prince-the-most-beautiful-girl-in-the-world/#more-23809|title=THE ARTIST FORMERLY KNOWN AS PRINCE \u2013 \u201cThe Most Beautiful Girl In The World\u201d|publisher=[[Freaky Trigger]]|date=2013-01-02|accessdate=2020-03-06}}</ref> Lars Nielsen from ''[[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]]'' called it a \"pop-pearl\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://gaffa.e-pages.pub/titles/gaffa/9520/publications/136/pages/22|title=Prince: Come|magazine=[[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]]|date=1994-09-01|page=23|accessdate=2020-03-29|language=Danish}}</ref> Alexis Petridis from [[The Guardian]] said \"it's a deft homage to the super-soft 70s soul of the Delfonics and the Stylistics\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/sep/12/prince-50-greatest-singles-ranked|title=Prince's 50 greatest singles \u2013 ranked!|magazine=[[The Guardian]]|date=2019-09-12|accessdate=2020-03-22}}</ref> Mark Carlson from ''[[The Michigan Daily]]'' picked it as one of the \"highlights\" from the album and described the song as \"super-sappy (yet somehow wonderful)\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://books.google.no/books?id=CBBKAAAAIBAJ|title=RECORDS: The Artist Formerly Known as Prince - The Gold Experience|magazine=[[The Michigan Daily]]|date=1995-10-02|accessdate=2020-03-15}}</ref> John Kilgo from ''The Network Forty'' said that the single \"may be Prince's strongest since \"[[Cream (Prince song)|Cream]]\"\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Network-40/94/Network-40-1994-03-11.pdf|title=Mainstream: Music Meeting|magazine=The Network Forty|date=1994-03-11|page=24|accessdate=2020-03-29}}</ref> In 2012, ''Porcys'' listed the song at number 5 in their ranking of \"100 Singles 1990-1999\".<ref>{{cite web|title=100 Singli 1990-1999|url=http://www.porcys.com/ranking/100-singli-1990-1999/10/|website=Porcys|date=2012-08-20|language=Polish|accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref> Tim Marsh from ''[[Select (magazine)|Select]]'' noted that it \"displayed a confident touch\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://selectmagazinescans.monkeon.co.uk/showpage.php?file=wp-content/uploads/2014/06/albums43.jpg|title=Reviews: New Albums|magazine=[[Select (magazine)|Select]]|date=1994-09-01|page=100|accessdate=2020-03-03}}</ref>     \n\n== Personnel<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.princevault.com/index.php?title=The_Most_Beautiful_Girl_In_The_World|title=The Most Beautiful Girl In The World - Prince Vault|website=www.princevault.com|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> ==\n\n* [[Prince (musician)|Prince]] - all vocals and instruments, except where noted\n* [https://www.rickypeterson.com/ Ricky Peterson] - additional keyboards (as \"Ricky P.\")\n* James \"Jimi\" Behringer - additional guitar\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" was directed by Prince and American film director and producer [[Antoine Fuqua]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://imvdb.com/video/prince/the-most-beautiful-girl-in-the-world|title=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World (1994) by Prince|publisher=IMVDb.com|accessdate=2018-10-18}}</ref>\t\n\n==Track listings==\n;Single\n# \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" (single edit) \u2013 4:06\n# \"Beautiful\" (single edit) \u2013 3:54\n\n;United Kingdom 12\"\n# \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" \u2013 4:07\n# \"Beautiful\" \u2013 3:57\n# \"Beautiful\" (extended club mix by [[Simon Harris (musician)|Simon Harris]]) \u2013 6:25\n# \"Beautiful Beats\" - 3:30\n\n== [[Plagiarism]] case ==\n[[Bruno Bergonzi]] co-wrote with [[Michele Vicino]] the song \"Takin' Me to Paradise\", published on 1983 by [[Warner Chappell Italy]]. The session vocalist was Raynard. J, the pseudonym of Jay Rolandi. The song appeared on a number of compilations, which was internationally distributed. An Italian court ruled on 2003 that [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]'s 1994 hit, \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\", was a plagiarism from the song by the two Italian writers. Bergonzi and Vicino won on appeal in 2007. The third and final sentence, by the [[Supreme Court of Cassation (Italy)|Court of Cassation]] of Rome, arrived in May 2015. Italian collecting society SIAE recognizes Bergonzi and Vicino as the authors of \"The Most Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" music.<ref>Mark Worden, ''Prince's Italian Plagiarism Case Drags On'', [https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7445762/princes-italian-plagiarism-case], Retrieved 10 February 2019. Roger Nelson Prince, Controversy Music inc., Michele Vicino, Bruno Bergonzi, [https://www.dirittodautore.it/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/SentCassCiv11225_2015.pdf]. Retrieved 16 April 2019.</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1994\u20131995)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|5|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|4|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|3|chartid=2491|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Denmark ([[IFPI Danmark|IFPI]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1994/MM-1994-05-07.pdf|title=Top 10 Sales in Europe|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=11|issue=19|page=13|date=May 7, 1994|access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles|Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1994/MM-1994-05-07.pdf|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|work=[[Music & Media]]|date=May 7, 1994|accessdate=March 31, 2018}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Finland ([[The Official Finnish Charts|Suomen virallinen lista]])<ref>{{cite book|first=Jake|last=Nyman|year=2005|title=Suomi soi 4: Suuri suomalainen listakirja|edition=1st|publisher=Tammi|location=Helsinki|isbn=951-31-2503-3|language=Finnish}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|5|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|9|songid=2775|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Iceland ([[\u00cdslenski listinn|\u00cdslenski Listinn Topp 40]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timarit.is/files/12119223.pdf#navpanes=1&view=FitH|title=\u00cdslenski Listinn Topp 40 (07.04.1994 \u2013 13.04.1994)|publisher=Dagbla\u00f0i\u00f0 V\u00edsir \u2013 T\u00f3nlist|accessdate=March 13, 2018}}</ref>\n| 15\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|4|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Italy (''[[Musica e dischi]]'')<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1994/MM-1994-05-21.pdf|title=Top 10 Sales in Europe|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=11|issue=21|page=24|date=May 21, 1994|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|1|year=1994|week=23|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|4|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Poland ([[Lista Przeboj\u00f3w Programu Trzeciego|LP3]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://lp3.polskieradio.pl/notowania/?rok=1994&numer=641|title=Notowanie nr641|publisher=[[Lista Przeboj\u00f3w Programu Trzeciego|LP3]]|language=Polish|date=May 27, 1994|accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n| 14\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|5|date=19940416|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|AFYVE]])<ref>{{cite book |last=Salaverri|first=Fernando|title=S\u00f3lo \u00e9xitos: a\u00f1o a a\u00f1o, 1959\u20132002|edition=1st |date=September 2005|publisher=Fundaci\u00f3n Autor-SGAE|location=Spain|isbn=84-8048-639-2}}</ref> \n| 1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|13|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|1|artist=The Symbol|song=The Most Beautiful Girl in the World|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKsinglesbyname|1|artist=Prince|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 2, 2016}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=Hot 100}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: The Billboard Hot 100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B Singles]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=R&B/Hip-Hop Songs}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Mainstream Top 40]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=Pop Songs}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: Pop Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US [[Rhythmic (chart)|Rhythmic Top 40]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite journal|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Prince|chart=Rhythmic Top 40}}|title=Prince \u2013 Chart History: Rhythmic Top 40|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 3\n|}\n\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1994)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia (ARIA)<ref name=\"ausye\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/annual-charts/1994/singles-chart|title=1994 ARIA Singles Chart|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]]|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| 23\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Belgium (Ultratop Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1994|title=jaaroverzichten 1994|language=Dutch|publisher=Ultratop|accessdate=December 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| 16\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.2687&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.2687.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.2687|title=RPM Top 100 Hit Tracks of 1994|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]]|accessdate=September 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| 41\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Europe (Eurochart Hot 100)<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1994/MM-1994-12-24.pdf|title=1994 Year-End Sales Charts: Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|accessdate=November 28, 2019|work=Music & Media|format=PDF}}</ref> \n| 17\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|France (SNEP)<ref>1994 French Singles Chart [http://www.disqueenfrance.com/fr/monopage.xml?id=259376&year=1994 Disqueenfrance.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110820065025/http://www.disqueenfrance.com/fr/monopage.xml?id=259376&year=1994 |date=2011-08-20 }} (Retrieved January 30, 2009)</ref>\n| 28\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1994|title=Top 100 Singles \u2013 Jahrescharts 1994|language=German|publisher=[[GfK Entertainment]]|accessdate=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n| 46\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.top40web.nl/jaarlijsten/jr1994.html|title=Jaarlijsten 1994|language=Dutch|publisher=Stichting Nederlandse Top 40|accessdate=November 29, 2019}}</ref>\n| 6\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1994&cat=s|title=JAAROVERZICHTEN - Single 1994|language=Dutch|publisher=dutchcharts.nl|accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|New Zealand (Recorded Music NZ)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/index.php/chart/?chart=3883|title=End of Year Charts 1994|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Sweden (Sverigetopplistan)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/43?dspy=1994&dspp=1|title=\u00c5rslista Singlar, 1994|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|language=Swedish|accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n| 76\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/charts/jahreshitparade/1994|title=SCHWEIZER JAHRESHITPARADE 1994|accessdate=December 4, 2019|publisher=hitparade.ch}}</ref> \n| 15\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1994|title=''Billboard'' Top 100 Hits for 1994|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref>\n| 19\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Mayte version==\n[[Mayte Garcia]] later recorded her own version called \"The Most Beautiful Boy in the World\". The song appears on her album ''[[Child of the Sun (album)|Child of the Sun]]''. It has the same instrumental backing track with extra reverb, and her vocals, with a few slight ad-lib changes. It was released by [[NPG Records]].\n\n==Cover versions==\n*In 1998, rapper [[Raheem the Dream]] sampled the song to make his own track, also titled \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\".{{cn|date=April 2018}}\n*In 2003, pianist [[Alex Bugnon]] covered the song on his album ''Southern Living''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.narada.com/images/AlbumPage/SouthernLiving/southernliving_page.htm|title=Southern Living|publisher=[[Narada Productions|Narada.com]]|accessdate=March 31, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706204534/http://www.narada.com/images/AlbumPage/SouthernLiving/southernliving_page.htm|archivedate=July 6, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://jazztimes.com/reviews/currents/alex-bugnon-southern-living/|title=Southern Living Alex Bugnon|magazine=[[JazzTimes|JazzTimes.com]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n*In 2013, artist [[Bruno Mars]] covered the song during [[The Moonshine Jungle Tour]].{{cn|date=April 2018}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n*Uptown: ''The Vault \u2013 The Definitive Guide to the Musical World of Prince'': Nilsen Publishing 2004, {{ISBN|91-631-5482-X}}\n\n==References==\n{{